    <h2>The Challenge</h2>
    <p>MISC Berhad, one of the world's leading providers of energy-related maritime solutions, required a comprehensive asset integrity management system for its Mero 3 FPSO, destined for operation in the pre-salt fields offshore Brazil. The complexity of a newbuild FPSO, combined with stringent Brazilian regulatory requirements and the operator's high standards for safety and environmental performance, demanded a proven AIM solution that could be deployed from day one of operations.</p>
    <p>Implementing AIM during the commissioning phase, rather than retrofitting after years of operation, presented both an opportunity and a challenge. The opportunity was to establish data quality and integrity workflows from the outset. The challenge was coordinating with multiple shipyard contractors, equipment vendors, and engineering teams to capture baseline data during a hectic construction and commissioning schedule.</p>

    <h2>The Solution</h2>
    <p>Metegrity partnered with MISC to deploy <strong>Visions Enterprise</strong> as the integrated AIM platform for Mero 3. The implementation began during the construction phase, with equipment data loaded from vendor documentation and engineering databases. Baseline thickness measurements were captured during construction inspections and loaded directly into the system, establishing day-one corrosion monitoring capability.</p>
    <p>The platform was configured to meet both MISC's corporate integrity standards and the specific requirements of Brazil's National Agency of Petroleum, Natural Gas and Biofuels (ANP). Damage mechanism assessments were completed for all circuits based on design process conditions, providing a risk-ranked inspection plan ready for the start of operations.</p>

    <h2>The Results</h2>
    <p>Deploying AIM from commissioning delivered significant advantages over the typical retrofit approach:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Complete baseline data from day one</strong>, eliminating the years of data gaps that plague retrofit implementations.</li>
      <li><strong>Risk-based inspection plan operational at startup</strong>, avoiding the default to conservative time-based inspection during the program ramp-up period.</li>
      <li><strong>Reduced implementation cost by 40%</strong> compared to estimated retrofit costs, by avoiding the expense of retrospective data gathering and system population.</li>
      <li><strong>Full regulatory compliance demonstrated at first ANP audit</strong>, with complete inspection records and documented risk assessments available on demand.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>A Model for Newbuild AIM</h2>
    <p>The Mero 3 implementation established a replicable model for deploying AIM on newbuild assets. By engaging the AIM provider during the engineering and construction phase, operators can capture data that would be expensive or impossible to reconstruct later. This approach is now being adopted across MISC's fleet of FPSOs, creating a standardized integrity management framework that supports consistent performance across all assets.</p>
    <p>The project demonstrated that the incremental cost of early AIM engagement is far outweighed by the long-term benefits of comprehensive baseline data and operational readiness from day one.</p>
